# Done

Finalize a done-ready change: run a fresh G_ship gate check and archive the
governed bundle to `artifacts/changes/archived/<slug>/`. `done` never removes the
git worktree — uncommitted non-bundle files are left for you to commit alongside
the archived bundle.

## Invocation
```bash
slipway done
# or
slipway done --all-ready
```

## Contract
- Only call when the change has reached DONE-ready state.
- `--all-ready` archives every active change that is currently done-ready.
- CLI checks the G_ship gate before archiving; if it fails (e.g. stale
  evidence), it surfaces blockers and a remediation (often `slipway run`).
- On success, surface the archive path and any non-blocking
  `worktree_dirty_warning` / `worktree_dirty_files` so the operator commits those
  files with the archived bundle; `done` does not remove the worktree.
- Show archived change summary to user.

## Flags
- `--all-ready`: Archive every active change that is done-ready (cannot be combined with `--change`)
- `--change <slug>`: target a specific active change (cannot be combined with `--all-ready`)
